Wien Air Alaska is your passport to the Great Land!
From the incomparable beauty of Alaska's Arctic to the former gold rush town of Fairbanks in the Interior, from the cosmopolitan city of
Anchorage to picturesque Kodiak in the Southwest, from the gateway of Seattle to Boise, Salt Lake, Portland, Phoenix, and Denver, Alaska's
first airline can take you to more than 150 Alaskan destinations, and beyond. Consider Wien's Best of Alaska Tour Destinations for 1982.
Cross the Arctic Circle
See the midnight sun and request Wien's Arctic Circle Certificate in your name.
Kotzebue / Nome - Eskimo dances, craft demonstrations, and shopping. Kotzebue's
famous "Living Museum of the Arctic." History and romance of the gold rush days... gold
panning in Nome.
Point Barrow - "Top of the World" — Northernmost point on the North American conti-
nent and whaling capital of the Arctic. Stand on the shores of the Arctic Ocean. See an
Eskimo blanket toss, ceremonial dances and craft demonstrations.
Prudhoe Bay - Learn about Arctic ecology with a visit to the origin of the famous Trans-
Alaska Pipeline.

Diverse Alaska
National Parks - More than 7 National Parks are easily accessible from our gateways.
Visit Katmai National Park, a majestic wilderness where glacial ice and volcanic fire meet
with incredible beauty. From Wien's wilderness lodge, see the Valley of 10,000 Smokes.
Enjoy spectacular hiking, wildlife, and photography.
Angler's Paradise - Enjoy some of the finest freshwater fishing and wilderness explora-
tion in the world from one of our comfortable wilderness lodges. Write for a free Angler's
Paradise brochure.
Wien's Alaska Passport: Unlimited Mileage*
Now you can explore more of the real Alaska for less than you'd ever imagine. Here's
how it works: Two or more people must travel together; plan your own itinerary to cover
as much territory as you can / up to 15 Alaskan destinations. Validity period 15 days for
U.S. /Canadian residents; effective until September 30, 1982. As low as $599 from
Seattle; $779 from Boise; $855 from Salt Lake; $809 from Denver;
$898 from Phoenix; $665 from Portland.
